Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on stone block, showing figures of four gazelles (probably Dama gazelle) and one unidentified quadruped, all upright and facing right, gazelle figures pecked in outline and partially infilled with pecking on neck, shoulders and rump. 10cm photo scale fitted at base of image. New Kalabsha, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
